.subsubsection Toolbar Buttons

The detailed functioning of all sections, ranging from progress notes to past history, referral letters etc 
is discussed in detail later. The default startup screen in the clinical section is a new general progress notes page. Note that if 
the section requested by the button click is already in the workspace then the tab will switch to that section. If you can design icons 
please feel free to donate your time to replace this terrible collection.



.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_new_general_progressnotes_page.png
.nobullets
.item 
.bold New General Progress Notes Page
- Loads a new progress notes page, general notes only should go here.
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_past_history.png
.nobullets
.item
.bold Past History
- enter details of the patients problems or health issues, past present, active, inactive
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_requests.png
.item
.bold Requests
- create request forms for anything you designate, e.g pathology, radiology, physiotherapy etc. see
.xref Allocating Categories 
 in the Other Contacts section 
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_referrals.png
.item
.bold Referrals
- type referrals to other providers e.g a specialist referral letter
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_prescription.png
.item
.bold Prescriptions
- write prescriptions, currently only available to valid MIMS subscribers
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_recalls.png
.item
.bold Recalls
- enter recalls and reminders for example pap smears, colonoscopies, annual checkups etc.
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_progressnotes.png
.item
.bold Review Progress Notes
- shows all existing progress notes which you may filter according to problem if you wish
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_careplan_summary.png
.item
.bold Care Plan Summary
- displays the patients care plan
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_print.png
.item
.bold Print
- prints the contents of the currently displayed section (if applicable)
.end imagetext
.imagetext clinical/gui/maintoolbar/button_save.png
.item
.bold Saves any outstanding data
- note the F12 key will also call this function
.end imagetext

In future releases the available buttons will be user configurable.

